\q1
\v 9 People who are considered to be unimportant are \add as worthless/unreliableas\add* a breath of air;
\q2 people who are considered to be important also really ◄amount to nothing/cannot be trusted\add to help us►\add*.
\q1 If you put them all on a scale, \add it would be as if\add* they weighed less than a puff of air.
\q1
\v 10 Do not trust in money gained by extorting it from others;
\q2 do not try to gain anything by robbing others.
\q1 If you become very wealthy, do not trust in [IDI] your money.
